channel.title: CVE Feed for Microsoft -- Microsoft Edge (EdgeHTML-based) on Windows 10 Version 1809 for 32-bit Systems
channel.description: The latest CVEs for Microsoft -- Microsoft Edge (EdgeHTML-based) on Windows 10 Version 1809 for 32-bit Systems

item.title: CVE-2019-1427|2024-08-04T18:20:27.437Z -- microsoft -- microsoft%20edge%20%28edgehtml-based%29%20on%20windows%2010%20version%201809%20for%2032-bit%20systems
item.description: A remote code execution vulnerability exists in the way that the scripting engine handles objects in memory in Microsoft Edge (HTML-based), aka 'Scripting Engine Memory Corruption Vulnerability'. This CVE ID is unique from CVE-2019-1426, CVE-2019-1428, CVE-2019-1429.

item.title: CVE-2019-1299|2024-08-04T18:13:30.369Z -- microsoft -- microsoft%20edge%20%28edgehtml-based%29%20on%20windows%2010%20version%201809%20for%2032-bit%20systems
item.description: An information disclosure vulnerability exists when Microsoft Edge based on Edge HTML improperly handles objects in memory, aka 'Microsoft Edge based on Edge HTML Information Disclosure Vulnerability'.
